<hl>
<seg id=1> Infrastructure projects become the hotspot for the foreign investors in Qinghai province. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xining, Dec. 21- (Xinhua News Agency) The city infrastructure here, which formerly restricted the foreign investment, now becomes a newly rising field significant in attracting foreign investment for Qinghai Province after the rush of natural resource exploitation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The infrastructure of Xining lacks investment in a very long period of time. In the 46 years ever since the founding of the People's Republic till 1995, the capital input into the infrastructure of the city only totals RMB 0.4 billion. The back lag of the city infrastructure largely confines its economic development. </seg>
<seg id=4> In recent years, some of the foreign companies expressed their interest in participating the construction of Xining. </seg>
<seg id=5> The government of Qinghai province made use of this opportunity to bring forward the thought of commercialization of the city construction and ratified the Provisions for Encouraging and Guiding Foreign Investment in Xining early this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> As soon as the government decided to invite foreign companies to manage the operation of the east exit roads of Xining with reasonable returns, a dozen of them bid for the project, and the deal was finally decided on RMB 50,000,000. </seg>
<seg id=7> A Hongkong company solely contracted the Mojia Street Reform Project, which demands modern city functions and designs. </seg>
<seg id=8> The 6th Water Source Construction Project attracted foreign funds about RMB 20,000,000, and will be able to supply 150,000 tons of water daily, which will greatly alleviate the water shortage of the Xining city. </seg>
<seg id=9> The government had reached agreement with the Hongkong Taihua Corp. on the construction project of the north exit roads of the city, which requires a total investment of RMB 0.18 billion. The south circular highway project is also bid by several foreign companies. </seg>
</p>
